<Author>SafariBart
<Content>Almost perfect ! We stayed 2 nights in September in a Terrace Room. The whole property has a great ambiance and beautiful design. Although there are around 30 rooms, the layout guarantees a very intimate and private impression. The room itself was standard size (around 25 to 30 square meter) and from the terrace we had a wonderful view over the valley. Bathroom is absolutely wonderful with a sunken bathtub and outdoor shower. Breakfast was wonderful and 脿 la carte. Two minuses though : 1) Sun loungers around the pool : When the hotel is fully booked, it can be quite difficult to find two loungers next to each other. Moreover, at every time of the day there are usually only a handful of loungers in the sun... rest is shaded. As a result, loungers in the sun are always taken or 'reserved'.2) Shuttle service caused some stress and hassle : first of all, last shuttle is around 5 PM which creates a problem if you want to go a restaurant downtown in the evening. Secondly, there are two pick-up / drop-off locations downtown and it happened that the car was full when we wanted to return to the hotel in the afternoon. Anyhow, we had a great time in Ubud. 
