<Content>Flawless The Uma Ubud is the perfect place to rediscover a sense of balance, as advertised on the website.One arrives to cool face towels beautifully scented with peppermint and eucalyptus, the trademark scent of Como Shambhala before being whisked away on a tour of the spa, restaurant and room all set in tranquil gardens surrounded by pristine nature.The service here is first class - nothing is too much for the staff and I never saw a frown regardless of question or task. The staff members here are clearly well trained and financially rewarded.The resort has an infinity edge pool backed by a lounge and bar (the perfect place to while away the time and enjoy one of the many books in the library); a gym; an excellent restaurant and a Como Shambhala spa perfect for those that desire a little pampering. There is also an business area with internet access computers for those that cannot ignore the distractions of work. The rooms are filled with wonderful Como Shambhala products, a beautiful bed, balcony, TV and everything else one could desire during a stay here including full-size fluffy bath towels and mineral water. In all, this place is recommended for all who are looking for a little tranquility in Bali. It makes a pleasant respite from the busy roads and markets and it truly is a place to enjoy a more peaceful experience. 
