<Content>Over rated We stayed at Uma Ubud in mid June for 6 nights. We must say the place is nice and clean, staff are friendly and the service is good. There is complimentary morning walks to the padi fields, yoga classes and free shuttle to the ubud centre. But most of the resorts in ubud provide those frills anyway. We do think the resort is slightly overrated. We had stayed in nicer places in Langkawi and Krabi. The decor of the place is quite minimal and utilitarian. There is only one restaurant in the resort. The menu is rather limited, the food generally is very average but there are one or two very nice dishes. You will get better and tastier meals outside the resort. There were some bed bugs and sandflies which left us with some very nasty bites. There were no mosquito problems since there is a mosquito netting around the bed. The resort still uses mosquito coils in the rooms instead of an electrical insect repellent which is very unhealthy and certainly not good if you have respiratory problems. The spa menu is also slightly on the high side and it is certainly not better than any of the massages we had before. In fact, we think the massage was rather mediocre. However, overall we did have an enjoyable stay. Although, we are unlikely to revisit Uma unless the package is very competitive. 
