<Content>A nice place to stay in Ubud Uma is a wonderful place to stay in Ubud. We stayed there on a short stopover in Bali, and didn't want to spend lots of $$ staying at the Four Seasons. It's very good value at less than half the price of the Four Seaons or Amandari. The rooms are actually half a standalone villa, with your own small garden terrace. We were lucky because we actually had the best view of the valley/terraces from our room. You don't get your own pool but that's OK. The bath products from the Como Shambala spa are excellent. Didn't get a chance to do the spa but will definitely try next time.The hotel is on the main thoroughfare in Ubud, so it's very convenient and a short walk to restaurants like Mozaic (highly recommended), or the center of Ubud town. 
