<Content>Honeymoon Heaven My husband and I ended our honeymoon at Uma Ubud because we wanted the last hotel to be something really special. We were not disappointed! We stayed in one of the pool villas overlooking the river canyon which was beautiful. The room was spotless and huge! Great four post canopy bed, living room, dining room, extra large bathroom (with the best shower pressure!) and comfy chairs on the porch. Unfortunately it rained everyday we were there (mid December) so we didn't get to take advantage of the private pool as much as we had hoped but the hotel provided free DVDs and there was great room service. There's a shuttle into town (about 5-10 minutes) everyday that you have to pay for, which is disappointing at this price level, but always on time. Ubud is a gem! Great stores, art galleries, dance performances, etc. Take the rice paddy walk through the hotel--its almost completely flat and the tour guide was very knowledgeable about farming practices and local culture. For a real treat, splurge at Mosaic, a restaurant down the street. Its expensive but you get a multi-course dinner that is unbelievable. 
